	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I remember Metal Storm fondly.  It had such potential, in terms of graphics and gameplay.   The game even had a spread in Nintendo Power, touting its unique gameplay.  Most notably, the parallax background scrolling and "switchable" gravity were way out there for the time.
<br />
<br />But its execution was strangely lackluster, it had garish palettes, so-so music and the stages were quite repetitive.  Also, some of the later stages were heavily twitch-based, which leads to some extreme frustration given you have limited lives and continues.
<br />
<br />I would have loved to see this game redone as a more shooter-style SNES game.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
